theorem
(for X being  bounded  commutative BCK-algebra holds (for a being (Element of X) holds (a is  being_greatest implies (X is  BCK-implicative iff (for x,y,z being (Element of X) holds ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ z ) ))))))
proof
let X being  bounded  commutative BCK-algebra;
let a being (Element of X);
assume A1: a is  being_greatest;
thus (X is  BCK-implicative implies (for x,y,z being (Element of X) holds ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ z ) )))
proof
assume A2: X is  BCK-implicative;
let x being (Element of X);
let y being (Element of X);
let z being (Element of X);
X is  BCK-positive-implicative  BCK-positive-implicative BCK-algebra by A2,CKB55:1;
then A3: ( ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ ( x \ z ) ) ) \ ( ( x \ y ) \ z ) ) = ( ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ ( x \ z ) ) ) \ ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) ) by CKB45:def 1
.= ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:1;
( ( ( x \ y ) \ z ) \ ( x \ y ) ) = ( ( ( x \ y ) \ ( x \ y ) ) \ z ) by BCIALG_1:7
.= ( z ` ) by BCIALG_1:def 5
.= ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:def 8;
then A4: ( ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ ( x \ z ) ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) = ( 0. X ) by A3,BCIALG_1:3;
( ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) \ ( x \ ( a \ z ) ) ) = ( ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) \ ( z \ ( z \ x ) ) ) by A1,A2,CKB69:1
.= ( ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) \ ( x \ ( x \ z ) ) ) by CKB1:def 1
.= ( 0. X ) by A4,BCIALG_1:7;
hence thesis by BCIALG_1:def 11;
end;

assume A5: (for x,y,z being (Element of X) holds ( ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ z ) ));
(for x being (Element of X) holds ( ( a \ x ) \ ( ( a \ x ) \ x ) ) = ( 0. X ))
proof
let x being (Element of X);
( ( x \ ( x \ x ) ) \ ( x \ x ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ x ) ) by A5;
then ( ( x \ ( 0. X ) ) \ ( x \ x ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ x ) ) by BCIALG_1:def 5;
then ( x \ ( x \ x ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ x ) ) by BCIALG_1:2;
then ( x \ ( 0. X ) ) <= ( x \ ( a \ x ) ) by BCIALG_1:def 5;
then x <= ( x \ ( a \ x ) ) by BCIALG_1:2;
then ( x \ ( x \ ( a \ x ) ) ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:def 11;
hence thesis by CKB1:def 1;
end;
hence thesis by A1,CKB65:1;
